utors' diverse perspectives by noting common themes, similarities, and differences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh1 aApplebaum, Anne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMiller, Jane Ann08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300147933423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300147933.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles